message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
title: "rlhf-compact-llm: An end-to-end RLHF pipeline for compact open-source LLMs"
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Tseng
    given-names: Yu-Hsuan
repository-code: "https://github.com/jujuliaa12/rlhf-compact-llm"
url: "https://github.com/jujuliaa12/rlhf-compact-llm"
identifiers:
  - description: SFT LoRA adapter on Hugging Face Hub
    type: url
    value: "https://huggingface.co/julia569922/qwen2.5-0.5b-rlhf-sft"
  - description: Reward model LoRA adapter on Hugging Face Hub
    type: url
    value: "https://huggingface.co/julia569922/qwen2.5-0.5b-rlhf-rm"
  - description: PPO-aligned LoRA adapter on Hugging Face Hub
    type: url
    value: "https://huggingface.co/julia569922/qwen2.5-0.5b-rlhf-ppo"
abstract: >-
  An end-to-end Reinforcement Learning from Human Feedback (RLHF) pipeline
  built on Hugging Face TRL, targeting compact open-source language models
  such as Qwen2.5-0.5B and SmolLM2-1.7B. Covers supervised fine-tuning,
  reward modeling on Anthropic HH-RLHF, PPO-based alignment, and an
  evaluation harness for studying reward hacking and verbosity bias at
  sub-1B scale.
keywords:
  - rlhf
  - llm
  - ppo
  - reward-modeling
  - lora
  - alignment
  - qwen
